description.narrative: By 2024, an improved knowledge base/baseline that inform programming and advocacy initiatives to increase access to birth certificates and to prevent and protect children and women from violence, abuse and exploitation, which contributes to Learning, Skills, Participation And Engagement, Prevention Of Harmful Practice, Promotion Of Care, Mental Health And Psychosocial Well-Being And Justice, Protection From Violence, Exploitation, Abuse And Neglect. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Community Engagement, Social And Behaviour Change, Data, Research, Evaluation And Knowledge Management, Evaluations, Research And Data, Fostering Innovation And Use Of New Technologies, Innovation, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2024, boys and girls In Liberia have access to quality prevention and response services for violence, abuse and exploitation and for birth registration.
